# User Registration Success Flow:

01. User ne Registration form fill kiya aur Sign Up button par click kiya.

02. Request UserRegistrationCtl par gayi aur BaseCtl ki service() method call hui.

03. service() method me operation parameter nikala gaya aur validate(request) call hua.

04. validate() method ne sab input fields check kiye aur validation successful (true) return kiya.

05. Control UserRegistrationCtl ke doPost() method me gaya.

06. doPost() method me populateBean(request) call hua aur UserBean object create hua jisme form data set hua.

07. UserModel ka object banaya gaya:
    UserModel model = new UserModel();

08. model.add(bean) method call kiya gaya.

09. UserModel.add() method me:
    - Duplicate check hua (findByLogin)
    - Koi duplicate nahi mila

10. nextPk() method se next primary key generate ki gayi.

11. Database connection liya gaya aur autoCommit false kiya gaya.

12. PreparedStatement banaya gaya aur user data insert kiya gaya:
    insert into st_user values(...)

13. pstmt.executeUpdate() call hua aur record database me successfully insert ho gaya.

14. conn.commit() call hua aur transaction commit ho gaya.

15. Control wapas UserRegistrationCtl ke doPost() method me aaya.

16. ServletUtility.setBean(bean, request) call kiya gaya taaki entered data JSP par show ho sake.

17. ServletUtility.setSuccessMessage("Registration successful!", request) set kiya gaya.

18. ServletUtility.forward(getView(), request, response) call hua.

19. Request wapas UserRegistration.jsp par forward hui.

20. JSP par:
    ServletUtility.getSuccessMessage(request) se "Registration successful!" message display hua.
